//Tendons - patellar tendon

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 08 - Soft parts of Knee MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Tendons - patellar tendon' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled
And 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tear' checkbox
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled
And 'Retraction' checkbox is enabled
And 'Surrounding haematoma' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone bruise' checkbox is enabled
And 'Patella alta' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Distal' radio button
Then 'Avulsion tibial tuberosity' checkbox is enabled
When I select 'Retraction' checkbox
Then 'Dimension in mm' input field is enabled

When I select 'Enthesiopathy' checkbox
Then 'Proximal' radio button is enabled
And 'Distal' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Proximal' radio button
Then 'Sinding-Larsen-Johansson Syndrome' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening / edema of the distal patellar ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Edema of the infrapatellar fatty body (Hoffa)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema of the inferior patellapol' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Thickening / edema of the distal patellar ligament' checkbox
Then 'Deep' checkbox is enabled
And 'Superficial' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Distal' radio button
Then 'Morbus Osgood-Slatter' radio button is enabled
And 'Previous Morbus Osgood-Schlatter' radio button is enabled
And 'Non specific patellar tendinopathy "jumper's knee"' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Morbus Osgood-Slatter' radio button
Then 'Thickening / edema of the distal patellar ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema of tuberosity (apophysitis)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis infrapatellaris profunda ("clergyman's knee")' checkbox is enabled
And 'Edema of the ventral soft tissues' checkbox is enabled
And 'Unsharp caudal margin of the infrapatellar fat body ("Hoffa fat pad" sign)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Fragmentation of tuberosity' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Previous Morbus Osgood-Schlatter' radio button
Then 'Bursitis infrapatellaris profunda ("clergyman's knee")' checkbox is enabled
And 'Irregularity of tibial tuberosity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening / edema of the distal patellar ligament' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Non specific patellar tendinopathy "jumper's knee"' radio button
Then 'Thickening / edema of the distal patellar ligament' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bursitis infrapatellaris profunda' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema of tuberosity (apophysitis)' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intratendinous calcification' checkbox is enabled
And 'Traction spur' checkbox is enabled